        @Deprecated
public void register(int id,
                                  ResourceLocation name,
                                  I thing)
        Deprecated. register through GameRegistry instead.
        Add an object to the registry, trying to use the specified id. This is required, to re-route vanilla block and item registration through to the add(int, net.minecraft.util.ResourceLocation, I) method.

      • getId

        public int getId(I thing)
        Get the id for the specified object.

        Don't hold onto the id across the world, it's being dynamically re-mapped as needed.

        Usually the name should be used instead of the id, if using the Block/Item object itself is not suitable for the task.

        Parameters:
        thing - Block/Item object.
        Returns:
        Block/Item id or -1 if it wasn't found.
